<br>
Ok, yesterday I dinged level 60.  Truth be told, I have been loving my Epic pet..and I have been enjoying playing a Mage after finally getting out of the frustrating lower to mid 50's levels.  <br>
<br>
I spent an hour LFG in the Planes of Power yesterday morning...no luck. So finally I modify my /shout to read as:  &quot;Level 60 Mage and his cantankerous Epic pet, LFG =)&quot;  The next thing I know is that other NON Epic Mages start /ooc and /shout &quot;The Epic sucks&quot;....&quot;The Epic is obsolete&quot;....&quot;You wasted your time getting the Epic...I didn't bother since it's useless now&quot;.  <br>
<br>
Interestingly enough, the night I got my Hate Staff and did the turn in for the Epic, I was in the Bazaar talking with a guildie.  He was congratulating me in /say.  I said &quot;Thanks so much&quot;...and out of the blue this level 62 Mage (Non Epic) starts in on me in /say about how much of a loser I am for even being excited to get the Epic since it's a few expansions old and a waste of time.<br>
<br>
I just don't understand where all of the Hate from fellow Mages is coming from.  Yes, I know the Epic is a Kunark quest..and is outdated a bit.  Yes, I know the 61 Air pet tears things up.  But damn it...I worked long and hard for the Epic...I didn't have much help....I do not brag about it and I am a relatively quiet player.  Whenever I am in an XP group, my pet gets compliments (Jabober always takes the adds in the Planes...and does quite nicely).  <br>
<br>
Have any of you experienced this?  For those that do not have the Epic and are not going to get it for whatever reasons you have, can you shed some light on why someone feels the need to belittle another for having the Epic?  Don't get me wrong...I have a lot of people come up to me and say, &quot;Is that the Epic?&quot;...and they have a million questions...that makes things very nice =)<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
Moon<br>
